r of John B. Hattendorf, for more than thirty years Ernest J. King Professor of Maritime History at the US Naval War College and an influential figure in naval affairs worldwide. N.A.M. Rodger is Senior Research Fellow at All Souls College, Oxford. J. Ross Dancy is Assistant Professor of Military History at Sam Houston State University. Benjamin Darnell is a D.Phil. candidate at New College, Oxford. Evan Wilson is Caird Senior Research Fellow at the National Maritime Museum, Greenwich. Contributors: Tim Benbow, Peter John Brobst, Jaap R. Bruijn, Olivier Chaline, J. Ross Dancy, Benjamin Darnell, James Goldrick, Agustín Guimerá, Paul Kennedy, Keizo Kitagawa, Roger Knight, AndrewD. Lambert, George C. Peden, Carla Rahn Phillips, Werner Rahn, Paul M. Ramsey, Duncan Redford, N.A.M. Rodger, Jakob Seerup, Matthew S. Seligmann, Geoffrey Till, Evan Wilson  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNaval strategyxHistory. 4aEarly Modern History. 4aMaritime History. 4aMilitary History. 4aModern History. 7aHISTORY / Military / Naval.2bisacsh  aBritish Navy.  aBritish naval strategy.  aNROTC.  aROTC.  aWorld War II strategy.  ahistory of war.  amarines.  amaritime history.  amilitary history.  amilitary trategy.  anavy.  aoceanography.1 aBenbow, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrobst, Peter John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruijn, Jaap R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChaline, Olivier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDancy, J. Ross, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDarnell, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDarnell, J. Ross Dancy, Benjamin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/v